Trade Intelligence Manager — Architecture Document
1. System Philosophy
Current system: AI participates exactly once, at entry. After that, mechanical rules manage the trade. Intelligence ends when the position opens.
Target system: AI remains part of the trade for its entire lifetime. The relationship is:
Think → Execute → Observe → Reason → Adapt → Observe → Reason → Adapt → Exit → Learn
The foundational principle is separation of reasoning from execution:
Layer	Responsibility	Examples
AI (Reasoning)	Strategic intent	"Hold", "Increase protection", "Scale out 25%", "Exit"
Deterministic (Execution)	Safe translation	Calculate exact stop price from ATR, place order, validate bounds
The AI never calculates a stop-loss price. It says "tighten protection moderately," and the execution layer computes the precise number. The AI never touches order mechanics. It says "exit a quarter," and the execution layer places the correct order.
This is the opposite of a rule engine. We already have an LLM capable of reasoning. Use it for reasoning. Use deterministic code only where deterministic behavior is required — safety bounds, order validation, exchange compliance.
