3. Component Responsibilities
Trade Memory Manager
- Owns the three-tier memory model (Immutable Origin, Working Memory, Event Journal).
- Handles persistence and retrieval of all memory artifacts.
- Manages memory compression: triggers compression when thresholds are exceeded, invokes LLM for summarization, stores compressed summaries.
- Provides memory access APIs for Context Builder and Learning Extractor.
- Guarantees immutability of Origin (write-once, read-only after creation).
Thesis Manager
- Stores and provides access to the Original Thesis (loaded from Immutable Origin).
- Tracks the Current Thesis, Current Conviction, Current Market Narrative (in Working Memory).
- Performs deterministic checks against Original invalidation conditions after market data updates.
- When invalidation conditions fire, notifies the Review Lifecycle Coordinator to schedule an immediate AI review.
- Maintains conviction evolution history (time series embedded in Event Journal entries).
- Provides deviation metrics: how far is current market state from the original thesis expectations?
Review Lifecycle Coordinator
- Receives signals from the Review Scheduler.
- Enforces per-trade review locks (prevents overlapping reviews).
- Manages review priority queue.
- Orchestrates the sequence: Context Builder → ReasoningCoordinator → SelfCritique → Intent Validator → Strategic Intent Executor → Memory updates.
- Handles degraded modes (LLM unavailable → safe default behavior).
Context Builder
- Assembles the complete input for the AI review.
- Selectively loads from memory: Working Memory (full), Original Thesis (key sections, not full text), recent Event Journal entries (last N since last review or compression), compressed summaries (most recent).
- Fetches current market state: price, ATR, volatility regime, trend, correlation to anchor, volume.
- Fetches trade performance: unrealized PnL, MFE, MAE, holding time.
- Fetches trigger reason (why this review was requested).
- Ensures total context stays within token budget (configurable, e.g., 4000 tokens input). If budget exceeded, applies priority-based truncation with an explicit note to the AI about truncated data.
Intent Validator
- Receives parsed LLM output (structured intent).
- Validates action type is recognized and parameters are within allowed ranges.
- Checks internal consistency (e.g., cannot both HOLD and EXIT).
- Applies strategic bounds (e.g., cannot SCALE_OUT more than 100%).
- Returns validated intent or rejection with reason.
Strategic Intent Executor
- Transforms validated strategic intents into concrete actions.
- Maintains a mapping from strategic action types to execution procedures.
- Applies deterministic constraints: minimum stop distance, maximum adjustment per review, exchange compliance, risk bounds.
- Calls existing execution layer (ExecutionService, ProtectionCoordinator) for order placement.
- Returns execution result (success/failure + details).
- All outputs are journaled.
Trigger Monitor (external)
- Watches real-time data streams for trigger conditions.
- Categories: time-based, market-based (volatility regime, correlation breakdown, trend change, price level), performance-based (profit milestone, drawdown threshold, time decay), event-based (catalyst achieved, catalyst invalidated, invalidation condition, new evidence, risk event, manual intervention), recovery-based (post-restart).
- Emits typed trigger events with metadata (trigger type, trade ID, severity, data payload).
- Configurable per trade (some triggers can be enabled/disabled based on AI suggestion).
Review Scheduler (external)
- Receives trigger events from Trigger Monitors.
- Maintains a priority queue of pending reviews across all trades.
- Priority tiers: CRITICAL (preempts all, max 1 concurrent), HIGH (next available, wait up to 30s), NORMAL (wait up to 5min), LOW (wait up to 15min, can be batched).
- Enforces system-level bounds: minimum interval between reviews per trade (configurable, default 5min), maximum interval (configurable, default 4h).
- Respects per-trade review locks (one active review per trade at a time).
- Signals TIM when a review slot is available.
Learning Extractor
- Activated when a trade reaches CLOSED state.
- Collects: complete Immutable Origin, all Working Memory snapshots (or initial → delta → final), complete Event Journal (including compressed summaries), all AI review records, conviction evolution time series, strategic intents and their execution outcomes, market data price/volatility/correlation path for the trade's duration, final PnL and exit reason.
- Packages into a structured learning payload.
- Feeds into existing LearningPipeline (extract → validate → normalize → persist as LearningManifest).
- Additionally feeds into a new ReasoningEvolutionAnalyzer that specializes in analyzing reasoning evolution across the trade lifespan.
